transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Who am I speaking with?

Speaker 1: My name is Michelle.

Speaker 2: Michelle, Mark Schneider. How are you?

Speaker 1: Good. How are you doing, Mark?

Speaker 2: Good. I'm a little stressed out, but I'm sure I'm going to get some answers here.

Speaker 1: I had called you guys a week or two ago.

Speaker 2: I tried to cancel my subscription. You charged me $63.95 again.

Speaker 1: Okay, Mark. Can you just confirm your date of birth?

Speaker 2: I'm sure it's March 17, 1961.

Speaker 1: Thank you so much. Okay, let's see what's going on.

Speaker 2: When I called to talk to the gentleman, he said he was going to credit me the amount and he was going to send me some new and improved…

Speaker 1: Why did he only send you $10 and not $30?

Speaker 2: He wasn't supposed to charge me anything.

Speaker 1: He says, I'm going to send you this as a trial.

Speaker 2: He says, I'm not going to charge you because you've been a VIP customer.

Speaker 1: Yeah, and then I see the notes from our pharmacy. They can't FedEx to a P.O. box.

Speaker 2: Hold on. I'll refund you right now. Give me a second.

Speaker 1: Michelle, I need a $63.95 refund. I've canceled this thing.

Speaker 2: If I just send the product back, it doesn't work for me, so I don't care about that.

Speaker 1: I'm going to toss it in the garbage.

Speaker 2: So you received the AGV, right? The replacement from the 16th?

Speaker 1: Let me double check.

Speaker 2: Yeah, take out the pill because the AGV, the only number imprinted on the AGV is the number 100.

Speaker 1: And those aren't working for you either?

Speaker 2: These aren't the 100. So I just got these.

Speaker 1: So these I just received. I haven't tried those yet.

Speaker 2: Can I put you on a brief hold really quick?

Speaker 1: Yep.

Speaker 2: Hold on one second. Thank you.
